<font color="#FF0000">VET66 AND AOL</font><br>
<tt>Thu Feb 13 19:13:43 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I had the privilege of exchanging poetry by e-mail with Joe during a dark time in my life. It was a spontaneous thing, one late night in an AOL chat room with 5 people. Joe's verses really stuck with me, even though I was only 7 yrs old when the Vietnam War was called off. It seems AOL is so much into providing &quot;clean entertainment&quot; that it has lost sight of what it takes sometimes to tell the truth about our lives. Our lives are not &quot;clean and wholesome&quot;. To regulate our language in order to &quot;prevent&quot; from offending others has gone to the degree of &quot;sterilizing&quot; our language, and creating obstacles to sharing the truth with Joe and others. Perhaps those who choose to monitor our language should try to read it with understanding rather than with a rulebook.
<p><code>-- peregrinn@aol.com  (Joel Hernandez) </code><p>


